LOOP CONTROL:
	PASS: Pass statement does nothing, it can be used when a statement is required syntactically but the program required no action

>>> string='India'
>>> for i in string:
...     if i=='d':
...             pass
...     print('Current letter is:', i)
... 
Current letter is: I
Current letter is: n
Current letter is: d
Current letter is: i
Current letter is: a
>>> 
